Description: Fragment of oval handle at neck join from a probably Chian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine light red-brown. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Timakles. Same die as Chr. Börker and J. Burow, Die hellenistischen Amphorenstempel aus Pergamon, Berlin, 1998, no. 609. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 173, 9.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0047)
